m Number Four\n|\nThe best lies are based on thetruth, at least in part\n\n- Cassandra Clare, Clockwork Angel\n|\nDid God ever cry over his lost angel, I wonder?\n\n- Libba Bray, Rebel Angels\n|\nMoney is better than poverty, if only for financial reasons.\n\n- Woody Allen, Without Feathers\n|\nTried living in the real world instead of a shell, but I was bored before I even began.\n\n- Morrissey\n|\nI believe our clever young man has intuited that while only the pursuit of happiness is promised to all Americans, unhappiness is guaranteed for many.\n\n- Viet\n|\nPerfection is overrated, creativity is the genius and it's better to be considered crazy than to be boring.\n\n- Ane\n|\nNovels are food for the leftover hours of life, the in-between times, the moments of waiting.\n\n- Young-Ha Kim, I Have the Right to Destroy Myself\n|\nIt is a man's own mind, not his enemy or foe, that lures him to evil ways.\n\n- Gautama\n|\nI was raised among books, making invisible friends in pages that seemed cast from dust and whose smell I carry on my hands to this day.\n\n- Carlos Ruiz Zafón, The Shadow of the Wind\n|\nGive me an enthusiastic, purpose-oriented person and I will give a successful future leader.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhat's the difference?' You ask meThe difference is, a smile touches my lipsWhen I remember both the memory of you entering my lifeAnd the memory of you leaving my life\n\n- Tammy-Louise Wilkins, My Intimate Poetry\n|\nThe teaching must, of course, work with the best part of the individual, must be directed to his or her real capacity.\n\n- Idries Shah, Learning How to Learn: Psychology and Spirituality in the Sufi Way\n|\nBooks are boring,' James said as he wrote.'They line the walls like a thousand leather doorways to be opened into worlds unknown,' I offered.\n\n- Laura Whitcomb, A Certain Slant of Light\n|\nIn battle, it is not the strongest or the bravest or those with the greater numbers who win. Victory belongs to the side that best understands the price of defeat.\n\n- Shatrujeet Nath, The Conspiracy at Meru\n|\nArthur blinked at the screens and felt he was missing something important. Suddenly he realized what it was.'Is there any tea on this spaceship?' he asked.\n\n- Douglas Adams, The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy\n|\nIn life, everyone must decide in what area of life he or she wants to be great. You must choose what territory you want to conquer.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nBack then we gave it our all, we neither lied nor made mistakes, we didn't fail and didn't do anything wrong.It's just that...TIME has passed and changed it all.\n\n- Yuuki Obata, We Were There, Vol. 1\n|\nIf you don’t know where you are going, ask those who have been there.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nLife is too short, or too long, for me to allow myself the luxury of living it so badly.\n\n- Paulo\n|\nBut the second she opened her eyes and looked at me, I knew. She was either going to be the death of me . . . or she was going to be the one who finally brought me back to life.\n\n- Colleen Hoover, Ugly Love\n|\nThe truth is, the Devil's job is easy.\n\n- Tyler Edwards, Zombie Church: Breathing Life Back Into the Body of Christ\n|\nhit with your fist, not with your finger spread\n\n- Prasetya\n|\nIf all work and no play makes you dull,Then you're on the wrong job.\n\n- Innocent Mwatsikesimbe, Thoughts Unknown\n|\nIn fact, there are many uses of the innumerable opportunities a modern life supplies for regarding - at a distance, through the medium of photography - other people's pain.\n\n- Susan Sontag, Regarding the Pain of Others\n|\nNo matter how bad your heart is broken, the world doesn't stop for your grief.\n\n- Faraaz\n|\nStupidity and wisdom meet in the same centre of sentiment and resolution, in the suffering of human accidents.\n\n- Michel de Montaigne, The Complete Essays\n|\nWhen nobody interferes