rsevere if you are willing to lean on them.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nOne mind, One master.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWell, if it can be thought, it can be done, a problem can be overcome,\n\n- E.A. Bucchianeri, Brushstrokes of a Gadfly\n|\nSuccess is built on hard work, the right hard work itself is success.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nLike time suspended, a wound unmended-- you and I.  We had no ending, no said goodbye;  For all my life, I'll wonder why.\n\n- Lang Leav, Love & Misadventure\n|\nDo you love him?'There were only a few people in the world who could ask me such insanely personal questions without getting punched. Dimitri was one of them.\n\n- Richelle Mead, Last Sacrifice"